# After downloading the D-ITG

# Navigate to D-ITG Directory

#cd D-ITG-2.8.1-r1023

#cd src/

D-ITG-2.8.1-r1023/src# make

#dependencies will be checked 

# if dependencies are satisfied it will be correctly installed

cd D-ITG/bin

On the destination host type:

D-ITG/bin#./ITGRecv

#ITGRecv will open a listening socket for TCP/UDP traffic coming from the other nodes.

#In contrast, ITGSend is used to send a constant TCP traffic flow 
